INFORMATIONAL NOTICE<div>
Upon doing tests or further investigations that necessitate SN-107, make sure to follow all procedures emplaced by Rama Saom and the federal government to protect ''entities designated as national/patriotic symbols and/or serve as a substitute national animal''; additionally, on such occasions, authorization must be received from higher-ups.

> Overview

{{Blurimage|file=The silloid.png|caption=Crude sketch of SN-107 eating.|width=180px}}

Entity 107, or widely referred to as '''Corasil Sinos Arma''' (Heart of the Army), is a man-made construct of most definite [[Z.E.T.A.|ZETAN]] provenance. It bears the physical characteristics of a hound, [[Entity 3-A|Vulpes Lumina]], and other entities, which are thought to have appeared due to the extensive gene mixing done by Z.E.T.A. patriots, though these are merely theories created from files retrieved from the Hadius Blacksite Raid.

SN-107 does not present a direct danger to wanderers; despite possessing the ability to mutilate anyone or anything in mere seconds with its jaw or claws, due to its domestication caused by the Solace Program, it is unlikely the stated scenario to happen, unless it is directly commanded to attack or it perceives an individual as a threat. SN-107 also demonstrates medium levels of intelligence, being able to speak, albeit limitedly.

> Biology

SN-107, as previously mentioned, takes on the physical characteristics of various entities. Gene testing revealed that SN-107 included the DNA of at least 15 other lifeforms, with Smilers, Hounds, Gemini Lunares, Kats, The Cadejo, and Vulpes Lumina (which is believed to be the 'host' of all these genes) being some traced. Furthermore, its singlemost defining physical attribute—being the skull and antlers—are composed of an exceptionally strong material that was able to withstand an RPG shell; despite this, it was still knocked unconcious upon detonation, with the skull showing a 'bulge' downwards in the location where the explosive was detonated.

SN-107 bears the most resemblance to Vulpes Lumina, although it has several observable mutations. It is predominantly covered by black fur-like material, and additionally, it seemingly possesses no internal organs. Various objects have been extracted from its 'insides' in our search for them, ranging from bullets to artillery shells. The skull has 2 holes that function as eyes (despite being completely pitch black).

> Behavior

SN-107 behavior can only be explained as that of a dog: curious, playful, yet still raveneous in nature. The entity spends most of its time interacting with researchers and the military units (and, on rare occasions, the Auriellen populace) that are responsible for it, which naturally causes it to replicate their actions.

From information gathered from Test Uneo, whenever left alone, it'll usually roam around a space before sleeping, or it'll engage in some sort of activity such as learning more about English or [[Aurielleno]]. This had led to theories that, because of the nature of ZETAN tests that include genemixing and the results from the examination, SN-107 has some sort of human presence within it.

> Capabilities

SN-107 shows certain capabilities, which have made it a great asset for both Rama Saom expeditionary teams and researchers and the Auriellen Armed Forces. These are appropriately called 'Dacosi' (English: Dangersense) and 'Plorisbu" (English: Exodus). Dacosi is self-explanatory; it allows it to pre-emptively sense most types of danger. This was exceptionally useful during Operavito Casvino, with it 'sniffing' out field mines placed during the Korthie Casiagen War.

Plorisbu, on the other hand, allows it to easily navigate its way to an exit in most levels. Used in the 2018 Koshevski Evacuations, Valai Emergency, and crisis responses, as well as to find exits in dangerous levels.

> Retrieved file from the Hadius Blacksite Raid

Although a majority of the files were burned by ZETAN guardsmen, a set of documents were salvaged. Some thought to pertain to SN-107.

