> CORASIL SINOS ARMA

[[File:Universal Patch for the Task Force.png|250px|center|link=]]


Simbos Nacional-107, or "Corasil Sinos Arma," is to be protected at all costs under every circumstance. SN-107 is of utmost importance to the Auriellen people and military; upon any contact with a hostile force that threatens its existence, a considerable military response MUST be carried out. Despite its size and nimbleness, with its ability to possibly murder up to a company's worth of soldiers, given that one does not have armor penetrating systems, in roughly 2 hours, SN-107 is to be monitored at every moment by Task Force operators, which uphold the primary responsibility of keeping it safe. Operators must conduct weekly wellfare checks on the entity; they must NOT get far from it as well, with them upholding a distance of a maximum of 100 meters in open spaces and 5 meters from it in the scenario where vision is significantly reduced or in enclosed locations. Additionally, operators should remain on high alert for a possible ambush whilst guarding the entity.

SN-107 is to be protected by 3 distinct Task Forces, all utilizing the universal "Solar Cog" patch; these Task Forces are under the designation of Task Force Moira, Stiger Resrum, and Coronislo, which are all under the direct command of the Auriellen Security Council. Their main responsibility is to protect, teach, and interact positively with SN-107. Positive interactions are all that would incite a feeling of wellbeing in the entity; these include petting, feeding (regular food or treats), talking, and playing. It is the primary function of the task forces when they are considered off-duty; this is to further domesticate the entity.

In the unfortunate scenario of an ambush or planned attack on SN-107, all operators must abandon their previous objectives and under every circumstance protect the entity from the attackers. It should be noted that all explosive devices <u>should be destroyed immediately, and any enemy trooper possessing them should be the first to be killed. The timeframe in which this occurs should be some 10 minutes after the initiation of the attack.</u>

Under occasions of heightened political tensions, where the assassination of SN-107 would be number one priority in enemy war plans, the [[C24N Seborna|C24N1 Seborna]] Armored Personnel Carrier equipped with the experimental Rajah Active Protection System is to be fielded to the task force(s) to further protect SN-107. Additional restrictions on the distance are to be applied, and the Seborna APC should be at least 5 to 10 feet away from the armored vehicle to ensure proper protection from the APS. If possible, a number of 3-5 soldiers from the platoon-sized task forces will accompany SN-107 in a tank desant; accompanying forces alongside SN-107 will be located at the rear of the APC.

