<p style="color: #000; text-align: justify; font-family:Rasa;">  
The following text is intended for newer researchers that take on the principle of conducting authorized tests on SN-107, as well as operators of the Task Force. This does not excuse older members from reviewing the accompanying document to remember certain aspects of 'taking care' of SN-107. It should be clarified that this document is not pertaining to the military response in the event of an ambush against the entity; view Mendoveus Protactis for the conventional protocol in the case of that scenario.

----

<p style="color: #000; text-align: justify; font-family:Rasa;"> 
First and foremost, it is important to denote that making SN-107 perceive Auriellen symbols such as its flag, uniform, and patriotic symbols in a positive way should be number one priority in any position where one would be in the presence of SN-107 for elongated periods of time. To do so, niceness should be one's forthrightness when interacting with it. There are also several numbers of different methods to further grow and harden the cordial view of SN-107 on Aurielle and its allies. Some of which include:

<p style="color: #000; text-align: justify; font-family:Rasa;">  >Feeding, playing and generally being caring towards it.

<p style="color: #000; text-align: justify; font-family:Rasa;"> 
In the most simple construct, treat it as if it were a dog or companion. In terms of feeding, SN-107 is to be fed at least twice every 3 days, with a diet consisting of dead entities, recipes from a Wanderer's Cookbook, and, under occasions where rationing is necessary, dead bodies (of most likely M.E.G. descent). Though the deviation of the food served may be different, SN-107 is a carnivorous being, meaning that as long as the food being served is composed of mostly meats, it should not lead to any complications during feeding.

<p style="color: #000; text-align: justify; font-family:Rasa;"> 
Providing it with physical affection such as petting, 'belly-rubbing', and other forms of affection is recommended. These actions have somewhat therauptic impact on one, which is believed to be caused by the genes of Kat's found within SN-107. 

